Floppies are cheap, almost everybody's got them, and they're erasable,
unlike CDROM.  They also have the advantage that you can open the case
and drop the magnetic material in a paper shredder, which does a real
fine job of declassifying it, as well as making satisfying noises :-)
I've fed magtapes into paper-shredders - *boring* and slow!

